<a name="vote"></a>
<h3>Vote</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Click on "New Proposal" if you have a meal suggestion. Your suggestion will be added to the table where people can vote on it.</li>
    <li>Please vote for other meal proposals that you like, or click "Cook this!" to cook a meal!</li>
</ul>

<a name="eat"></a>
<h3>Eat</h3>
<ul>
    <li>To cook a new meal, go to the "Meals" page and click "Cook This!" for a meal proposal. Or, click on "Cook New Meal" directly and fill out the required information.</li>
    <li>To view information about a scheduled meal, click on "Details" in the corresponding row.</li>
    <li>Please click on "Help Cook" to aid our wonderful chefs. If you're no longer able to help, click "Won't Help".</li>
    <li>RSVP so that our chefs know much to cook. Please select "I'm coming!" if you plan to eat at the normal time, and "Pick up later" if you want a portion saved for you.</li>
    <li>To Un-RSVP, simply click again on the "RSVPed" status.</li>
</ul>

<a name="shop"></a>
<h3>Shop</h3>
<ul>
    <li>If you can commit to buying the materials of a meal, please click "Buy Materials" in the corresponding row. A dropdown menu of all your currently scheduled shopping runs will appear. Select which shopping run you will commit to buying the materials by.</li>
    <li>You can create a new shopping run by selecting the option from the dropdown menu, or by clicking the "New Shopping Run" button at the bottom of the page.</li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li>Click on the "Status" column label to separate all completed and pending shopping runs.</li>
    <li>To add materials for a meal to one of your shopping runs, click "Buy Materials" in the appropriate row above.</li>
    <li>To view information about a shopping run, click on "Details" in the corresponding row.</li>
    <li><b>To remove a meal from one of your shopping runs:</b> click on one of the listed meals in the "Meals to buy" column, and select "Remove".</li>
    <li>Once you finish a shopping run, click "Mark Completed" to enter your total payment amount.</li>
</ul>

<a name="credits_fees"></a>
<h3>Credit/Fees</h3>
<ul>
    <li>A person who cooks a meal will be awarded a credit of: $4 per night + an additional fee depending on the number of people eating that night.</li>
    <li>A person who helps cook a meal will be awarded a credit of: $4 per night.</li>
    <li>The maximum reimbursement of a shopping run is $75 per meal bought for, unless special approval is given.</li>
    <li>A person who performs a shopping run will be reimbursed fully (up to the restriction above).</li>
    <li>The base fee is $7 per night per meal. At the conclusion of IAP, if there are any remaining funds, they will be returned to you in proportion to the number of meals you have eaten.</li>
</ul>

